Method Detail

getFormalParameterDeclarations

java.util.List<FormalParameterDeclaration> getFormalParameterDeclarations()
Returns a list of the formal parameter declarations.

The last FormalParameterDeclaration object (or the only one) may be a vararg parameter declaration, i.e. a parameter declaration of a variable number of arguments like public void foo(anyType ... typeId) {...}.

Calling this method equals an getFormalParameterDeclarations(null) call.

Returns:
A list of the formal parameter declarations. If this represents an empty formal parameter list null will be returned.
See Also:
getFormalParameterDeclarations(List), FormalParameterDeclaration.isVarargParameterDeclaration()

getFormalParameterDeclarations

java.util.List<FormalParameterDeclaration> getFormalParameterDeclarations(java.util.List<FormalParameterDeclaration> pList)
Returns a list of the formal parameter declarations.

The last FormalParameterDeclaration object (or the only one) may be a vararg parameter declaration, i.e. a parameter declaration of a variable number of arguments like public void foo(anyType ... typeId) {...}.

Parameters:
pList - If this argument isn't null the formal parameter declarations will be added to this list and this list object will be returned. Otherwise a new list will be created for the result.
Returns:
A list of the formal parameter declarations. If this represents an empty formal parameter list null will be returned, even if the argument pList isn't null.
See Also:
FormalParameterDeclaration.isVarargParameterDeclaration()

isEmptyFormalParameterList

boolean isEmptyFormalParameterList()
Tells if the formal parameter list is empty, i.e. if there are no formal parameter declarations.

Returns:
true if the formal parameter list is empty.

replaceFormalParameter

void replaceFormalParameter(FormalParameterDeclaration pOldParameterDeclaration,
                            java.lang.String pNewParameterDeclaration)
                            throws JSourceObjectizerException
Replaces a certain parameter declaration by a new one stated as string.

Parameters:
pOldParameterDeclaration - The parameter declaration that should be replaced.
pNewParameterDeclaration - The new parameter declaration.
Throws:
JSourceObjectizerException - if the stated old parameter doesn't exist or if parsing the new parameter declaration fails.
